<div class="row section">
  <div class="col s12">
    <h2>Finding Help</h2>

    <p>If you are a victim of hate crime or know someone who is, there are various organisations that can offer support and guidance. You can find more information on these websites:</p>

    <div class='section'>
      <h5><%= link_to 'True Vision', 'http://www.report-it.org.uk/home', target: '_blank' %></h5>

      <p>True Vision is a police funded website designed to provide you with information about Hate Crime. It includes an <%= link_to 'extensive list of organisations', 'http://www.report-it.org.uk/organisations_that_can_help', target: '_blank' %> that can provide information and support.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='divider'></div>

    <div class='section'>
      <h5><%= link_to 'Victim Support', 'https://www.victimsupport.org.uk', target: '_blank' %></h5>
      <p>Victim Support is the leading independent charity for people affected by crime in England and Wales. Their services are free, confidential and available to anyone in England and Wales, regardless of whether the crime has been reported or how long ago it happened.</p>
    </div>

    <div class='divider'></div>

    <div class='section'>
      <h5><%= link_to 'Citizens Advice', 'https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk', target: '_blank' %></h5>
      <p>Local Citizens Advice offer advice from over 3,500 locations across the UK. These include high streets, community centres, doctors' surgeries, courts and prisons.</p>
      <p>Advice can be given in person, by phone or by email.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>